Britain's Queen Elizabeth II sits on the Sovereign's throne in the House of Lords as she delivers the Queen's Speech at the State Opening of Parliament in the Houses of Parliament in London on Monday. The State Opening of Parliament is where the queen performs her ceremonial duty of informing parliament about the government's agenda for the coming year. Photo: AFP 
